<!-- 
A quick guide to the Tailwind CSS classes we used:
- `bg-gray-900 text-white`: Sets the background and text colors.
- `p-6 md:p-8`: Sets padding (6 units on mobile, 8 units on medium screens and up).
- `border-b border-gray-700`: Adds a 1px bottom border.
- `container mx-auto`: Centers the content with a max-width.
- `flex justify-between items-center`: The core of the layout. Makes it a flexbox, pushes children to opposite ends, and vertically aligns them in the middle.
- `space-x-6`: Adds horizontal space between the nav links.
- `hover:bg-indigo-500`: Changes the background color when you hover over the element.
- `transition-colors`: Makes the color change smooth.
- `hidden md:flex`: The navigation is hidden on small screens (`hidden`) and becomes a flexbox on medium screens and up (`md:flex`). This is for mobile responsiveness.
-->